## Pre-Flight Tasks

### Critical (must complete before Mar 11)
- [ ] VPS auto-restart — wrap FFmpeg in shell loop so it restarts automatically if Restream drops connection
- [ ] Rebuild HoldtLoop.mp4 with `-g 12 -keyint_min 12` keyframe flags — fixes YouTube "Poor" stream health
- [ ] Harden VPS — change root password, create non-root sudo user, SSH key auth, disable root login

### On Arrival
- [ ] Get Greek SIM for AT&T hotspot at Athens airport (Cosmote or Vodafone Greece)
- [ ] Confirm GL-MT6000 power supply brick says Input: 100-240V
- [ ] Test wired internet → router → laptop before first stream

---

## Notes for AI Context

- **Primary streaming machine:** AERO X16 (AMD Ryzen AI 7 350, RTX 5070, 32GB DDR5, Windows 11)
- **Stream method:** VPS + FFmpeg for 24/7 lo-fi loop → Restream → YouTube + Twitch. OBS on laptop for live streams.
- **Internet:** Flatio apartment wired (195/19 Mbps confirmed) as WAN1. AT&T hotspot with Greek SIM as WAN2 failover via GL-MT6000.
- **Power redundancy:** TalentCell UPS keeps router stack alive on power drops. Anker 737 keeps laptop running.
- **Chat monitor:** iPad over WiFi — uses zero laptop ports.
- **Mac Mini M4 upgrade:** Not yet purchased. Planned upgrade for seamless lofi ↔ live switching. Home-base only (LAN-dependent). Deferred until streaming cadence validated post-Athens.
- **All stream source files** stored on SanDisk 2TB Extreme at `D:\StreamSourceFiles\`

